args: The Xihe should be enshrined\nsomewhere around here...
Ah, there it is! ...How interesting.\nI did not expect it to take the form\nof a garment.
Though it will certainly be easier to carry\nwith me if I can simply wear it.
Pray forgive us, Master Xuan Zang,\nbut we are here to stop you from claiming\nthat relic—by force, if necessary.
I told you both, this is my life's work!
Yeah, well, I guess we're not\na good pair of listeners.
So now there's you...and there's us.\nWhat say we have a little match\nto see who comes out on top?
If we are victorious, you will promise to\nthink veeeery carefully about the risks\nof taking up that relic.
You two truly never do listen...
We didn't come all this way just to\nlet you throw everything away!
I owe you a debt, and I'll do anything\nto pay it—including fighting you!
I'm actually excited to fight someone\nso powerful. Now let's do this! Haaaah!
Ah, ah, ah! I have already accounted\nfor you slithering off in that direction.
And now, to bind you in place...\nBehold the Thousand Hidden Arrows!
I should have expected no less from a fight\nwith commanders of Taiwu... However!
O power universal! Fire of the nine\nflames, stone of destruction,\nlet thy force be manifest!
Bwa ha ha! That's it?! I've been shootin'\ndown incendiary arrows in battle since\nI was a little kid!

(Their strength is impressive... And yet,
I cannot unleash the full force of my
relics here, lest I bring the entire cave
down upon our heads...)
(I will have to push my way through...\neven if it means pushing myself!)
Dammit! If we get stuck on the other side\nof this fire, she'll get the relic for sure!
I must do this... I must be willing to\nsacrifice all for the sake of those people!
Come on, we have to stop her!\nThere's still time!

O power universal of the Qilin,
be bound by my solemn decree.
Wealth of brilliance, ring of the sun!
Form a beam that incinerates all!
What IS that light?!\n...I can't avoid it! Argh!
Is this...the power of the Xihe...?
...Heh. Looks like someone\nwas pulling their punches.
He required a bit of first aid,\nbut should wake up his old self.
Damn. Here we thought we were being\nuseful, and you had to wade in and\nsave our sorry butts anyway.
Do not apologize for your actions.\nI know you did them on my behalf.
Still, it was hardly our best showing.
You did what you did out of kindness,\nwhich is why I apologize for causing\nyou to worry.
And yet, I will still bear the Xihe.
So long as there are people to protect in\nthis land, I will give all to see them safe.
Taking on the burdens of everybody\nisn't exactly the wisest life choice.
Perhaps. And yet, I have made\nmy peace with it.
I have borne many burdens that I was\nglad to carry during my life, after all.
Yeah, yeah, I get it. I lost. I'll shut up\nand letcha do whatever you want.
Hey! The nice lady's back!\nWhere've you been?
Oh, I just went for a little walk.\nAnd you? What did you do today?
Me and my sister planted our last seeds.\nIf they don't grow, then...
Um, do you think it'll rain?
Didn't I tell you that heaven will see\nhow hard you are all working?
Hee hee! Okay! I believe you!
We are CLEARLY outmatched\nwhen it comes to you.
Xuan Zang, we've detected another relic.
This ominous chi can only be that of the\nJin Gu Er, which we previously sealed.
It seems there has been some sort of\naccident... Has my seal come undone?
I will go and see at once. \nShow me the way, Yulong.
I have told you without ceasing that\nyou have nothing to do with relics.
Suppressing the abnormalities caused\nby relics is a duty for Qilin sealers.
Bwa ha ha! I hear that stock phrase of\nyours so much, I could say it in my sleep!
Look, you're a great person, and there's\nno way to count the lives you've saved.
But bearing responsibility for everything\nand anything like that isn't good for you.
It's like the wife always says to me:\nIf you're always trying to save everybody,\nyou eventually forget to save yourself.
No, I get it. We can't stop you.
But we ARE going to come with you.
And if you ever find yourself in a helpless\nspot, that's when I'll repay my debt to you.\nBecause that's what honor is.
And I shall also follow you to the\nvery ends of the earth!
And to think there are people who\nconsider ME to be stubborn...
Well then, it seems this is the beginning\nof a new journey for all of us.
That's just the kind of thing she would say\nbefore oozing off into the dark. We must\nnot let her leave us behind!
If she does, we'll just\nchase her down again.
Come and see. Both of you.
